Boil the peas in a pan of lightly salted water for 2-3 minutes, or until tender. Drain well, then rinse under cold running water.Roughly crush half the peas and blend the remaining into a smooth pur√©e using a hand-held blender.Mix the crushed and pureed peas together in a bowl, then stir in the tahini, lime juice, cumin and salt, to taste. Stir in the coriander and spring onions.Serve with vegetable crisps or tortilla chips.